name: Jay Cutler
summary: Former NFL quarterback Jay Cutler was arrested for driving under the influence (DUI) and gun possession following a minor car accident in Tennessee. According to police documents, Cutler's blood alcohol content was above the legal limit and he refused to take a breathalyzer test. He was also found to be in possession of a loaded handgun, which is illegal for him to have as a convicted felon. Cutler reportedly offered law enforcement officers $2,000 to let him go, but they declined. He was booked into the Williamson County Jail and faces charges of DUI, unlawful possession of a weapon, and bribery.

name: Woman of the Hour
summary: "Woman of the Hour" is a Netflix drama directed and starring Anna Kendrick. The film is based on the true story of Rodney Alcala, a serial killer who appeared on "The Dating Game" in the 1970s. Kendrick portrays a woman who suspects that her new boyfriend is the elusive killer, and the film follows her investigation into his past. Despite the chilling true story behind it, critics have mixed reviews. Some praise Kendrick's performance and the film's thought-provoking themes, while others find it dry and academic. The film has sparked interest in the case of Rodney Alcala, with many articles exploring the bizarre and disturbing details of his crimes. Kendrick herself has described the film as her "most revealing" ever, highlighting the personal and emotional toll the role took on her.

name: Tony Bennett
